{"metadata":{"name":"Sunan an Nasai","section":{"35":{"eng-name":"The Book of Agriculture","ara-name":"كتاب المزارعة"}},"section_detail":{"35":{"hadithnumber_first":3761,"hadithnumber_last":3856,"arabicnumber_first":3761,"arabicnumber_last":3856}}},"hadiths":[{"hadithnumber":3767,"arabicnumber":3767,"text":"It was narrated from 'Umar that the Prophet said:\"Allah forbids you to swear by your forefathers.\" 'Umar said: \"By Allah, I never swore by them again, whether saying it for myself or reporting of others","grades":[{"name":"Abu Ghuddah","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Al-Albani","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Zubair Ali Zai","grade":"Sahih - Agreed Upon"}],"reference":{"book":35,"hadith":7},"chapter":{"id":5,"ara-name":"باب الْحَلِفِ بِالآبَاءِ ","eng-name":"Swearing By One's Forefathers","isFirstHadith":false}}]}